{"title":"Sidi Physis XC Shoe Review: A Classic Brand Reboots for the Modern Rider","link":"https://bikerumor.com/sidi-physis-xc-shoe-review-a-classic-brand-reboots-for-the-modern-rider/","date":1747677146000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-pair--1536x1152.webp\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review pair\" /></p>\n<p>For a while, in the States, Sidi felt like a brand that had faded into the archives—hard to find, expensive when possible, and seemingly out of step with the modern cycling shoe market. But now, the legendary Italian shoemaker is making a serious comeback in North America with a new retail presence, better distribution, and three new models aimed at regaining their place in the pack. The new multi-discipline <a href=\"https://backcountry.tnu8.net/c/381569/358742/5311?u=https%253A%252F%252Fwww.backcountry.com%252Fsidi-physis-mountain-clipless-shoe-mens\">Sidi Physis off-road shoes</a> seemed like a good place to start, whether you are looking to ride gravel or XC. So we got in a pair to put them to the test…</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>The Sidi Comeback Plan: Better Availability &amp; Pricing</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-cover--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-cover--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review heel cover\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-cover--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-cover--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-cover--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-cover--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-cover--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-cover--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-cover--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a><figcaption><em>(All photos Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Sidi has partnered with QBP, North America’s largest cycling distributor, to return their shoes to local bike shops. This means easier access and more competitive pricing, although you shouldn’t expect bargain-bin deals. Although major online retailers like Backcountry, Velotech, Bicycle Addiction, and Jenson will also carry the new lineup.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Millennium  vs. Classic: A New Approach to Fit</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-both-shoes--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-both-shoes--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review both shoes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-both-shoes--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-both-shoes--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-both-shoes--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-both-shoes--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-both-shoes--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-both-shoes--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-both-shoes--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For years, Sidi’s standard ‘classic’ fit has been a love-it-or-leave-it experience—narrow, glove-like, and unforgiving for wider feet. But with modern high-performance shoes trending toward wider toe boxes, Sidi is adapting. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Introducing the Millennium Fit, a revised last that shortens and widens the toebox, creating a roomier feel without sacrificing performance.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-try-on-shot--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-try-on-shot--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review try on shot\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-try-on-shot--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-try-on-shot--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-try-on-shot--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-try-on-shot--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-try-on-shot--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-try-on-shot--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-try-on-shot--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For die-hard Sidi loyalists, don’t worry—the classic fit isn’t going anywhere. You’ll still be able to get that ultra-snug race fit if that’s your jam.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The New Lineup</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-side-1-1-scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-side-1-1-scaled.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-side-1-1-scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-side-1-1-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-side-1-1-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-side-1-1-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-side-1-1-768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-side-1-1-2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-side-1-1-1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3><em>Sidi Physis – Off-Road Performance</em></h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Millennium Fit for a roomier toe box</li>\n\n\n\n<li>TPU-welded fabric upper in Black or Sand (plus Violet &amp; Myrtus in the EU)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Single Tecno buckle + hook-and-loop strap for adjustability</li>\n\n\n\n<li>X2FC carbon outsole with a stiffness rating of 11/12 on Sidi’s scale</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Replaceable toe spikes &amp; full rubber tread for durability</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Price: $399 / 299€</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Genius-Knit-10.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1650\" height=\"1014\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Genius-Knit-10.png\" alt=\"Sidi Genius Knit 10\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Genius-Knit-10.png 1650w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Genius-Knit-10-297x183.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Genius-Knit-10-1536x944.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Genius-Knit-10-120x74.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Genius-Knit-10-768x472.png 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Image Sidi)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3><em>Sidi Genius 10 Knit – Hot Weather Road Shoe</em></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The new <a href=\"https://backcountry.tnu8.net/c/381569/358742/5311?u=https%253A%252F%252Fwww.backcountry.com%252Fsidi-genius-10-knit-road-shoe-mens\">Sidi Genius 10 Kint</a> is a road cycling shoe with a hybrid knit upper for ventilation and comfort.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Classic Sidi fit</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Hyper-vented nylon knit forefoot for breathability &amp; flexible comfort</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Available in Black or White (plus Violet in Europe)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Dual Tecno buckle closure system</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Nylon &amp; carbon composite sole with a stiffness rating of just 6/12</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Price: $355</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Ergo-6-.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1538\" height=\"914\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Ergo-6-.png\" alt=\"Sidi Ergo 6\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Ergo-6-.png 1538w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Ergo-6--297x177.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Ergo-6--1536x913.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Ergo-6--120x71.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Ergo-6--768x456.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3><em>Sidi Ergo 6 – The Modern Road Flagship</em></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The new <a href=\"https://backcountry.tnu8.net/c/381569/358742/5311?u=https%253A%252F%252Fwww.backcountry.com%252Fsidi-ergo-6-road-shoe-mens\">Sidi Ergo 6</a> brings an updated aesthetic and fit to the brand’s road cycling lineup.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Millennium Fit for a wider, more contemporary fit</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Clean, minimalist perforated microfiber upper with a dual Tecno buckle closure</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Available in White or Dark gray with reflective heel details (plus Burgundy &amp; Dark Blu in Europe)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Anchored Unum Ergo anatomical tongue design prevents shifting during rides</li>\n\n\n\n<li>New full-carbon R2FC outsole with a long 15mm of cleat adjustment range, 11/12 stiffness</li>\n\n\n\n<li>322g per shoe (size 44)—not the lightest, but competitive</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Price: $399 / 299€<br />*Look for a review on this model shortly</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Physis First Impressions</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-outside--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-outside--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review outside\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-outside--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-outside--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-outside--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-outside--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-outside--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-outside--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-outside--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Sidi Physis leads the charge, as a no-compromise MTB race shoe aimed squarely at XC and gravel riders who prioritize power transfer over walkability. So, is the Physis a worthy addition to Sidi’s legacy, or just another stiff shoe in an already crowded category?</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-outside-inner-shoe--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-outside-inner-shoe--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review outside inner shoe\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-outside-inner-shoe--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-outside-inner-shoe--297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-outside-inner-shoe--1536x1152.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-outside-inner-shoe--120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-outside-inner-shoe--768x576.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-outside-inner-shoe--2048x1536.webp 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>On the Bike with Physis</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Sidi shoes have always been known for impeccable craftsmanship, and the Physis is no exception. Out of the box, you can tell these shoes mean business. The seamless, dual-layer upper feels incredibly refined. And the Millennium Fit gives it a sleek, performance-driven shape, without being too tight.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-new-bottom--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-new-bottom--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review new bottom\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-new-bottom--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-new-bottom--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-new-bottom--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-new-bottom--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-new-bottom--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-new-bottom--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-new-bottom--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re expecting a casual, walkable MTB shoe, this is not it. The understated Physis screams race day when you put them on your feet. It is stiff, structured, and unapologetically designed for putting down watts.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Power Transfer &amp; Performance</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-toe-spikes--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-toe-spikes--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review toe spikes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-toe-spikes--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-toe-spikes--297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-toe-spikes--1536x1152.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-toe-spikes--120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-toe-spikes--768x576.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-toe-spikes--2048x1536.webp 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>At the heart of the Physis is the new X2FC full UD carbon sole, which is one step shy of Sidi’s stiffest rating. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Every bit of power you put down goes straight to the pedals. On the bike, the Physis feels explosive. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Whether mashing a climb or sprinting for the town line, you can feel the efficiency. The sole has zero flex, which is exactly what you want in a race-focused shoe.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-full-bottom-scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-full-bottom-scaled.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review full bottom\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-full-bottom-scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-full-bottom-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-full-bottom-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-full-bottom-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-full-bottom-768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-full-bottom-2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-full-bottom-1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For traction off the bike, Sidi adds molded-on rubber tread and toe spikes, but let’s be real—this is not a hike-friendly shoe. Walking on pavement or hard surfaces is almost laughable. If you expect to hoof it through long hike-a-bike sections, look elsewhere. Though thick lugs on the heel provide excellent grip for running down unrideable, cyclocross-style sections. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also worth noting is the extended rubber through the instep. That helps a lot if you unclip on some gnarly section, and it takes a moment until you can get your foot back over the pedal, and properly clipped-in again. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Millennium Fit &amp; Comfort – Snug, but Precise</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-front--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-front--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review front\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-front--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-front--297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-front--1536x1152.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-front--120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-front--768x576.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-front--2048x1536.webp 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Sidi describes its shoes as “fitting like a glove,” and that’s precisely how I’d describe them. The Physis is built with their new Millennium Fit, which adds a bit more room compared to traditional Sidi sizing. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>But it’s still a very snug, race-inspired fit. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The overall fit is wider, but not so much that it feels like a wide shoe, such as a Bont. I would just describe the fit as ‘more foot-shaped’ and less pointed at the toe box. Something that I’m sure all riders pushing hard on the pedals will appreciate.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-gripper--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-gripper--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review heel gripper\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-gripper--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-gripper--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-gripper--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-gripper--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-gripper--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-gripper--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-gripper--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I had to meticulously measure my feet and compare them to Sidi’s chart before ordering, and I still ended up in a size smaller than expected. When I first pulled them out of the box, they looked small, but once on, they fit like a second skin.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Sidi Strap &amp; Dial Closure System – Solid &amp; Secure</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-cover--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2300\" height=\"1294\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-cover-edited.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review heel cover\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-cover-edited.webp 2300w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-cover-edited-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-cover-edited-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-cover-edited-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-cover-edited-768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-cover-edited-2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-cover-edited-1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Sidi’s Solid-Strap closure system is a step up from your standard Velcro. Instead of relying on friction alone, it also features opposing plastic teeth that lock in place, eliminating strap tension loss over time. It’s been a minute since I used a shoe with a velcro-style strap. And with BOA dials flying off shoes at nearly every cyclocross race, I was interested. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-inner-buckle-scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-inner-buckle-scaled.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review inner buckle\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-inner-buckle-scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-inner-buckle-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-inner-buckle-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-inner-buckle-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-inner-buckle-768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-inner-buckle-2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-inner-buckle-1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The secure fit is a nice touch, and the soft fabric of the overlapping strap allows the shoe to flex easily when off the bike, even when running uphill.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-grirpper--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-grirpper--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review heel grirpper\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-grirpper--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-grirpper--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-grirpper--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-grirpper--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-grirpper--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-grirpper--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-heel-grirpper--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Paired with the Dyneema dial system across the forefoot and grippy silicone dots in the heel, the Physis offers a fine-tuned, locked-in feel. The strap keeps the foot stable, while the dial allows for micro-adjustments over the arch — crucial for preventing foot numbness.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-Made-in-Vietnam-scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-Made-in-Vietnam-scaled.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review Made in Vietnam\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-Made-in-Vietnam-scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-Made-in-Vietnam-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-Made-in-Vietnam-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-Made-in-Vietnam-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-Made-in-Vietnam-768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-Made-in-Vietnam-2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-Made-in-Vietnam-1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The tongue and edges were stiff from the start and pressed slightly against my ankle. However, over time and some rainy training rides, they softened up nicely.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tecno Buckle: A Love-Hate Relationship</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-dial--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-dial--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review dial\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-dial--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-dial--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-dial--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-dial--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-dial--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-dial--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-dial--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>One thing that hasn’t changed?</em> </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sidi’s proprietary Tecno buckle system. It’s been around longer than BOA, and while it still offers easy part replacements, it’s not as user-friendly or quick to adjust. You need two separate button presses to loosen or tighten, which may feel a bit outdated compared to BOA’s single-turn simplicity.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-toe-box--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-toe-box--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review toe box\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-toe-box--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-toe-box--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-toe-box--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-toe-box--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-toe-box--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-toe-box--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-toe-box--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>That said, Sidi fans will appreciate the durability and longevity that comes with the Tecno system — no risk of snapping a BOA wire mid-ride. Plus, replacement parts are very easy to find online, and a prepared rider might have some in their kit bag just in case.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Verdict: Who is the new Sidi Physis For?</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-tread-depth--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-tread-depth--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review tread depth\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-tread-depth--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-tread-depth--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-tread-depth--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-tread-depth--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-tread-depth--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-tread-depth--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-tread-depth--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://backcountry.tnu8.net/c/381569/358742/5311?u=https%253A%252F%252Fwww.backcountry.com%252Fsidi-physis-mountain-clipless-shoe-mens\">Sidi Physis</a> is a purebred racing shoe designed for XC, cyclocross, and gravel riders seeking maximum efficiency, durability, and a no-compromise fit. It’s the shoe for you if you’re looking for a lightweight, powerful shoe that will last for years. I have a pair of my first Sidi shoes still in a box, worked over from years of use, but I can’t seem to part with them.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>I’m hoping this new chapter for Sidi will deliver that same experience to new users, with an updated fit.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-cleat-mounted--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-cleat-mounted--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review cleat mounted\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-cleat-mounted--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-cleat-mounted--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-cleat-mounted--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-cleat-mounted--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-cleat-mounted--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-cleat-mounted--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-cleat-mounted--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Are they worth the $400 asking price? </em></p>\n\n\n\n<p>After many winter and spring rides in them, I lean toward yes. The shoes show minimal signs of wear, even though I washed them after almost every ride because of mud. However, for those seeking the top tier in the brand, this isn’t it for Sidi. They still have two models above this, topping out at <a href=\"https://backcountry.tnu8.net/c/381569/358742/5311?u=https%253A%252F%252Fwww.backcountry.com%252Fsidi-tiger-2s-mountain-clipless-shoe-mens\">$530 for the MTB Tiger</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>What do you get with a $530 mountain bike shoe that isn’t on a $400 one?</em> </p>\n\n\n\n<p>With Sidi, you get a super stiff carbon sole (almost too stiff), replaceable rubber tread blocks, and their super cool heel retention support system.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-weight--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"864\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-weight--1536x864.webp\" alt=\"Sidi Physis Review weight\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-weight--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-weight--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-weight--120x67.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-weight--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-weight--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sidi-Physis-Review-weight--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re a rider who loves the allure of a top-end Italian shoe (but it’s actually made in Vietnam, not made in Italy), with a bombproof build, and can handle all off-road racing, the Physis delivers in spades. This would be the perfect shoe for a racer or rider who’s tired of breaking BOAs (even if they do come with warranty replacement) and doesn’t like laces. We’re excited to see what this new chapter for Sidi brings – so far, it looks promising – and I’m here for it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://sidi.com/en-us/collections/xc\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Sidi.com</em></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/sidi-physis-xc-shoe-review-a-classic-brand-reboots-for-the-modern-rider/\">Sidi Physis XC Shoe Review: A Classic Brand Reboots for the Modern Rider</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"55e9d945dcab128f11cf10fdac4a7d7dceaaf715de2bb22556723024ba2b0014","category":"Cycling"}